description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come and join the friendly and welcoming Paediatric team on our Children’s Assessment Unit (CAU).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a &lt;strong&gt;Housekeeper &lt;/strong&gt;to work within the Jenny Lind Children’s Hospital at Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital. Our team are committed to ensuring we provide the highest standard of care to patients on the ward; you will work alongside all members of the multi-disciplinary team in order to ensure the smooth running of the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post-holder will receive training as required to fulfil this important role on CAU, where you will become part of well-established, dedicated and friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An organised person who can manage their time efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to prioritise workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 2 qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous work in a healthcare environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of cleaning as a paid profession.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As post holder you will be expected to undertake a range of duties including:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General cleaning of the ward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check equipment is cleaned and maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring stock levels are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all supplies and stationary are stored correctly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake a range of errands and work with the clinical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Housekeeper duty shift times vary between the hours of 07:30-17:30 and will require weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of a high quality, safe and compassionate healthcare service, all staff are expected to act as a role model to others in all aspects of their work and consistently demonstrate NNUH’s ‘PRIDE’ values of People focused, Respect, Dedication, Integrity and Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open for applications: 2nd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Close for applications: 6th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
